{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/cli-open","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"38233681-1a7e-55bb-bbf9-de46de08745c","html":"<p>This is a series of libraries and utilities for building Command-line-interfaces aka CLI using Node.js and ecosystem around it. Similar utilities/helpers may be available for other languages but, these series is focused on JavaScript and its friends.</p>\n<p>You can check all articles under <a href=\"/category/cli-build-tool/\"><code class=\"language-text\">CLI Build Tool</code></a> tag.</p>\n<h2 id=\"open\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#open\" aria-label=\"open permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/open\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">open</a></h2>\n<p>If you are building a CLI and need to open a file in external application or a URL in a browser, <code class=\"language-text\">open</code> is the package you need. The best part is, it is cross-platform. You can open stuff like URLs, files, executable(s) (across platforms), it also claims to be safer as it uses ‚Äòspawn‚Äô instead of ‚Äòexec‚Äô.</p>\n<p>You may have seen option to open your repository folder in your IDE, in Github Desktop App (Electron based). You can achieve such functionality using ‚Äòopen‚Äô</p>\n<p>‚ÄúOpen in Visual Studio Code‚Äù option in Github Desktop App.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a978dcb4ea7e81028ddfd8e4b0c0b135/82c1e/open.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.083333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/a978dcb4ea7e81028ddfd8e4b0c0b135/8ac56/open.webp 240w,\n/static/a978dcb4ea7e81028ddfd8e4b0c0b135/d3be9/open.webp 480w,\n/static/a978dcb4ea7e81028ddfd8e4b0c0b135/e46b2/open.webp 960w,\n/static/a978dcb4ea7e81028ddfd8e4b0c0b135/b391b/open.webp 1398w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/a978dcb4ea7e81028ddfd8e4b0c0b135/8ff5a/open.png 240w,\n/static/a978dcb4ea7e81028ddfd8e4b0c0b135/e85cb/open.png 480w,\n/static/a978dcb4ea7e81028ddfd8e4b0c0b135/d9199/open.png 960w,\n/static/a978dcb4ea7e81028ddfd8e4b0c0b135/82c1e/open.png 1398w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/a978dcb4ea7e81028ddfd8e4b0c0b135/d9199/open.png\"\n          alt=\"Screenshot\"\n          title=\"Screenshot\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">open</code> has a very easy to follow, simple to use API. Here is a code example:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> open <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'open'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Opens the image in the default image viewer</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">open</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'unicorn.png'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> wait<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">//wait option will wait for app to close</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'The image viewer app closed'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Opens the url in the default browser</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">open</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'https://sindresorhus.com'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Specify the app to open in</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">open</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'https://sindresorhus.com'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> app<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'firefox'</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Specify app arguments</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">open</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'https://sindresorhus.com'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> app<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'google chrome'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'--incognito'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>You can check out official <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/open\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">repo</a> for all usage details.</p>\n<p>Github Repo: <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/open\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">open</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#related\" aria-label=\"related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Related</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Check <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/open-cli\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">open-cli</a> - CLI version for this module</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/cli-open","tagSlugs":["/tag/cli/","/tag/tools/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-06-29T18:05:00.738Z","description":"Node.js CLI App helper for open a file in external application","tags":["CLI","Tools"],"title":"Tool of the Trade for CLI Apps - `open` üóÉ","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/cli-open"}}}